{
  "texts": [
    "These methods mainly fall under the category of similarity-based approaches.",
    "They rely on the assessment of similarity between drugs to infer potential interactions.",
    "In similarity-based approaches, drugs are compared based on their structural and chemical characteristics.",
    "Pairwise similarity measures such as the Tanimoto coefficient or the Jaccard distance are calculated.",
    "Higher similarity values indicate a higher probability of interaction between drugs."
  ]
}